name: Jumping Jacks
description: Adding arm circles to your workout routine helps to warm up the shoulders, arms, chest, and back. This is a great exercise to incorporate at the beginning of an upper body workout to prevent injuries and prepare your body for strength training.
tips: After you practice that and get comfortable with it rather than simply throwing your arms around, you could refine the circles further by adding rotations to the circles.
instructions: 1. Stand straight with your feet shoulder-width apart.
2. Raise and extend your arms to the sides without bending the elbows.
3. Slowly rotate your arms forward, making small circles.
